      "name": "Nafcillin",
      "brandNames": "Nallpen (discontinued brand), generic",
      "drugClass": "Anti-staphylococcal penicillin (penicillinase-resistant)",
      "mechanismOfAction": "Binds PBPs (particularly PBP2) inhibiting cell wall synthesis. Bactericidal, time-dependent killing (optimize fT>MIC). Designed to resist hydrolysis by staphylococcal penicillinase (beta-lactamase). This is the ORIGINAL anti-MSSA drug. Narrow spectrum by design — targets Staphylococci specifically, with minimal gram-negative or anaerobic coverage.",
